# Minimal depject + mutant?

I'm semi-familiar with using depject *once somebody else sets it up*, but I'm having trouble using it by myself. I want to get a list of people that I block, does anyone have time to give me  a hand? Here's what I've got so far:

```js
const combine = require('depject')
const patchcore = require('patchcore')
const mutant = require('mutant')

const api = combine([patchcore])

// using [0] to emulate depject's "first"
const id = api.keys.sync.id[0]()
const blockersObs = api.contact.obs.blockers[0](id)

const userBlocksThem = mutant.computed(blockersObs, (blockers) => {
  // this is never called
  return blockers.includes(id)
})

mutant.when(userBlocksThem, (blocks) => {
  // this is never called either
})
```

I *think* this is a Depject problem, but maybe it's a Mutant thing?

